overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to a detailed specification.
  The agent performed an in-depth analysis, identifying several critical missing
  features and areas for improvement. Subsequently, the agent systematically
  implemented these enhancements. Key additions included a dynamic 1-10
  tiredness severity scale with integrated safety warnings, advanced detection
  logic for complex sleep disorders like COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep
  Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and a refined weighted scoring system
  for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS). Furthermore, the CSV export
  functionality was significantly expanded to capture all questionnaire data,
  and new sections were introduced to screen for pain severity and chronic
  fatigue symptoms, complete with tailored recommendations. The agent ensured
  these changes were reflected across the application's types, validation
  schemas, UI components, API routes, and PDF report generation, providing a
  more robust and clinically relevant tool.
